      },
      "date": "2018-06-28 22:58:02.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\nIt might be useful if mdc_pack_body() renamed \"ea_size\" to \"ea_data_size\" so that this argument was more clear, and/or added a comment block to describe the arguments.\n\nFor example, what kind of flags the \"@flags\" argument is (looks to be LUSTRE_*_FL flags which are in a nameless enum that could be named and used as the argument type).",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "e5e46443069d3936ed190f0a46c7f017e3c4968d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2018-06-29 13:52:18.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> It might be useful if mdc_pack_body() renamed \"ea_size\" to \"ea_data_size\" so that this argument was more clear, and/or added a comment block to describe the arguments.\n\nI don't think this function should exist at all. None of the parameters have anything to do with each other. IMO this kind of function is a poor but common practice that saves the writer some time at the expense of the reader.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
